March Madness

Tracking Auckland’s bus delays
through its busiest month

Based on historical and real-time data, updated approximately every 30 minutes,
obtained from Auckland Transport’s public GTFS API

What is “March Madness”?

  • Busiest month of the year for public transport
  • Buses, trains at capacity
  • Industrial action: fewer trains during peak, which could increase bus demand

  • Starts February 26, when students surge into the CBD

  • The data:
    • real-time delays from buses
    • historical data from April through November 2017 for comparison

What does a typical day look like?

  • Peak periods: A morning, B school, C evening
  • The coloured areas represent the proportion
    of buses that are
    • more than 5 minutes early
    • on time (within 5 minutes of schedule)
    • late by more than 5 minutes

As of 8:00 am today

  • 585 of 888 buses were on time
  • 200 were running more than 5 minutes late
  • 103 were more than 5 minutes early

How does this compare?

  • data from April through November 2017
  • average percentage of buses early, ontime, or late,
    by time and day of the week
  • comparing today with the Tuesday average:
  • Expecting Auckland Transport to deploy more buses to cope with capacity
  • Could see higher proportion of late buses during March
